text: Anna M. Valencia (born January 16, 1985) is an American politician. She is the City Clerk of Chicago since 2017. She replaced Susana Mendoza. She was elected to a full term as City Clerk in 2019. Valencia unsuccessfully ran in the 2022 election for Illinois Secretary of State. ==References== Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from Chicago Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians
